postcontent:
Hello all I have for trade a Hungarian version of the ak47 the AMD 65. The Hungarians were the first Soviot Sataliet country to actually alter the original design of the AK. The internals are the same so you have the same AK to hell and back relibility, Ive seen savages in Afghanistan clean AKs with motor oil and boot strings and still have a reliable weapon. The first big thing they did was shorten the barrel, for tankers, troops in the rear, and for Airborne and Special Ops troops, however the nasty looking muzzle break is added to make the rifle 16inches so it can be US legal. The break serves this purpouse but also really tames the 7.62 recoil, which comes in handy for follow up shots. The foward grip is also a Hungarian add on, all it is is a backward pistol grip, but its very very easy to replace.

So basically you have an AK that is awsome at close quaters, easy to control, and in my opinion looks pretty sick. Its a nice setup, and thats not all included is a ULTIMAX scout rail, which is set up so it can co witness with most red dots so you always have a backup. title: For Trade:  Amd 65 ak47
postcontent:
Hello all I have for trade a Hungarian version of the ak47 the AMD 65. The Hungarians were the first Soviot Sataliet country to actually alter the original design of the AK. The internals are the same so you have the same AK to hell and back relibility, Ive seen savages in Afghanistan clean AKs with motor oil and boot strings and still have a reliable weapon. The first big thing they did was shorten the barrel, for tankers, troops in the rear, and for Airborne and Special Ops troops, however the nasty looking muzzle break is added to make the rifle 16inches so it can be US legal. The break serves this purpouse but also really tames the 7.62 recoil, which comes in handy for follow up shots. The foward grip is also a Hungarian add on, all it is is a backward pistol grip, but its very very easy to replace.

So basically you have an AK that is awsome at close quaters, easy to control, and in my opinion looks pretty sick. Its a nice setup, and thats not all included is a ULTIMAX scout rail, which is set up so it can co witness with most red dots so you always have a backup. Also comes with 5 mags and a few hundred rounds and a cheap TASCO red dot.
